FEDORA-2023-ab43e2ce21 has been pushed to the Fedora 39 stable repository.
If problem still persists, please make note of it in this bug report.

When ibus isn't running, kitty will fail to run with the following error message:

*** buffer overflow detected ***: terminated
Aborted (core dumped)

This happens on both F38 and F39. 

The author of kitty has been contacted but he couldn't reproduce the issue where he probably didn't use Fedora.
https://github.com/kovidgoyal/kitty/issues/6650

Therefore, this could either be a bug in kitty, or in the way how kitty is built on Fedora, or a lib used by kitty is vulnerable.

Reproducible: Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1.install kitty on F38 or F39
2.make sure ibus isn't running
3.run "kitty --config NONE"



Actual Results:  
*** buffer overflow detected ***: terminated
Aborted (core dumped)

Expected Results:  
Kitty should just work despite the unavailability of ibus and it shouldn't produce a buffer overflow error, which is very concerning from a security perspective.
